---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-saudi', text: 'Leaving Saudi Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'student-considerations', text: 'Student Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best UK Expat Insurance', href: '/best/uk-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'arabicSupport', header: 'Arabic Support' },
  { key: 'usNetwork', header: 'US Network' },
  { key: 'saudiCoverage', header: 'Saudi Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', usNetwork: 'Strong', saudiCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'SAR 750/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', usNetwork: 'Excellent', saudiCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'SAR 850/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Arabia', arabicSupport: 'Full', usNetwork: 'Good', saudiCoverage: 'Included', price: 'SAR 650/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', arabicSupport: 'Limited', usNetwork: 'Good', saudiCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'SAR 700/mo' },
  { provider: 'Tawuniya', arabicSupport: 'Full', usNetwork: 'Limited', saudiCoverage: 'Included', price: 'SAR 500/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Saudi Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Saudi nationals abroad. Find coverage for the US, UK, Europe, and other destinations for students, professionals, and families."
  headline="Best Insurance for Saudi Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Saudi nationals studying, working, or living abroad need proper healthcare coverage. Here's how to stay protected in the US, UK, and beyond."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/saudi-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Saudi nationals abroad include students, professionals, business owners, and families. Many destinations—especially the US and UK—require comprehensive coverage. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Saudi expats. Strong US and UK networks, Arabic support, comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Arabic support through Middle East operations.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Arabia:</strong> Saudi-based Bupa with international products. Full Arabic support, includes Saudi coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>Tawuniya:</strong> Major Saudi insurer with some international options. Full Arabic service.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="US Student Coverage"
    description="Many Saudi students study in the US on government scholarships. While some scholarships include insurance, coverage quality varies. Understand your coverage and supplement if needed—US healthcare costs are extreme."
    buttonText="Get US Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-saudi">Leaving Saudi Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Saudi Arabia has both public and private healthcare. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Public Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Saudi citizens have access to public healthcare facilities in the Kingdom. This coverage doesn't extend internationally—you need separate insurance for healthcare abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Saudi Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Saudi companies (Bupa Arabia, Tawuniya, Medgulf) typically provides limited international coverage—usually emergency treatment abroad. Living overseas long-term requires dedicated international coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Government Scholarship Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Saudi government scholarships (SACM) often include health insurance for students abroad. Coverage varies by program—review your specific coverage carefully. Some students supplement with additional international insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Employer-Sponsored Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Some Saudi employers provide international coverage for employees posted abroad. Verify terms and consider whether supplemental coverage is needed.
  </p>

  <h2 id="student-considerations">Student Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Many Saudi nationals abroad are students. Key considerations:
  </p>

  <h3>SACM (Saudi Arabian Cultural Mission)</h3>
  <p>
    Students on government scholarships through SACM may have provided insurance. Coverage details vary—understand what's covered and what's not. Some students find the provided coverage inadequate for US healthcare costs.
  </p>

  <h3>University Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    US and UK universities often require health insurance. Provided coverage may meet minimum requirements but not provide optimal protection. Review coverage levels carefully.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Students with families need coverage for spouse and children. Scholarship insurance may not adequately cover family members—international insurance ensures everyone is protected.
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage During Breaks</h3>
  <p>
    Consider coverage during summer visits home and travel. International insurance covers you globally; scholarship insurance may have limitations.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">US Healthcare Costs</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      US healthcare is the world's most expensive. A single hospital stay can cost $50,000-$200,000+. Ensure your coverage is comprehensive—basic student plans may leave significant gaps.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Saudi nationals abroad. Strong networks in the US and UK—the most popular Saudi expat destinations. Arabic support available through Middle East operations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited. Saudi coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Saudi expats who want reliable coverage with strong US/UK networks and Arabic support.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Service quality is outstanding. Arabic support available.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Best for those who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Saudi professionals and families who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Arabia</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Arabia is Bupa's Saudi operation, offering international products for Saudi nationals abroad. Full Arabic service, familiar brand, Saudi coverage included automatically.
  </p>

  <p>
    International networks are good, leveraging Bupa's global presence.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Saudi expats who prefer Arabic service with seamless home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe and adequate coverage elsewhere.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Saudi expats seeking good value, especially for European destinations.
  </p>

  <h3>Tawuniya</h3>
  <p>
    Tawuniya is Saudi Arabia's largest insurer and offers some international products. Full Arabic service, familiar brand, Saudi coverage included. International networks are more limited.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Saudi expats who prefer familiar Saudi service and primarily need Saudi coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get quotes from multiple providers. If you have scholarship insurance, understand what's covered before assuming you need nothing more."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Saudi nationals abroad have specific destination patterns:
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Largest destination for Saudi students, with tens of thousands studying across the country. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. Many cities have Saudi student communities.
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Popular for students and professionals. NHS provides healthcare to legal residents, but many supplement with private insurance for faster access. London has a significant Saudi community.
  </p>

  <h3>Europe</h3>
  <p>
    Growing destination for students and business. EU countries have public healthcare for legal residents. Private insurance supplements public coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>UAE and Bahrain</h3>
  <p>
    Close neighbors with Saudi business connections. Healthcare infrastructure is good. Some Saudis maintain coverage that works across GCC countries.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does Saudi insurance cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Saudi insurance provides limited international coverage (emergency only). Living abroad requires dedicated international health insurance for proper coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is scholarship insurance enough?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Coverage varies by program. Review your specific policy carefully. Some students find it inadequate for US costs and supplement with additional international insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage for my family?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">International insurance covers spouse and dependent children. Scholarship insurance may not adequately cover families—verify coverage for each family member.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Saudi visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Bupa Arabia and Tawuniya include Saudi coverage automatically. International insurers offer Saudi as a coverage region.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Arabic support important?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Many Saudi expats are multilingual, but Arabic support can help during stressful medical situations. Bupa Arabia and Tawuniya offer full Arabic service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Bupa Arabia or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Bupa Arabia offers Arabic service and includes Saudi coverage. Cigna has broader global networks. Choose based on destination and language preference.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Saudi nationals abroad need comprehensive international insurance. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for strong US/UK networks with Arabic support. <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage for those wanting the best.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Arabia</strong> suits those who prefer Arabic service with included Saudi coverage. <strong>Tawuniya</strong> works for those wanting familiar Saudi service.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you have scholarship insurance, understand exactly what it covers. US healthcare costs can be devastating without proper coverage—don't assume basic insurance is enough.
  </p>

</PageShell>
